http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/Dhanush%E2%80%99s-%E2%80%98Kodi%E2%80%99-to-be-wrapped-up-in-February/article14013945.ece

Actor Dhanush’s next Tamil outing Kodi, which went on the floors earlier this month in Pollachi, will be wrapped up in a jiffy by February.“The principal shooting will be completed by February 21. The following few weeks will be spent on post-production work,” a source from the film’s unit told IANS.The film is being directed by Durai Senthil Kumar.“As Dhanush plans to start working on a new project from March, he wants to complete Kodi as early as possible,” the source added.In the film, which also stars Shamlee and Trisha Krishnan, Dhanush plays dual roles.The movie’s story is reportedly set against the backdrop of a political turmoil.